From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: georgewhewell <georgerw@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 4 May 2026 00:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] thunderbolt: xdomain: log unmatched protocol UUIDs

When an XDomain control packet arrives whose header UUID does not match
any registered protocol handler, the dispatcher currently drops it
silently. That makes it impossible to discover what UUID a peer is
using for a service whose advertised directory UUID we know but whose
control-packet protocol UUID we do not.

Log the unmatched header UUID, the cfg packet type, the size, the
XDomain protocol type, and the first 32 bytes of payload (ratelimited).
Informational only -- packet handling is unchanged.

Used to discover Apple AD/FA57 control-packet UUIDs.

Signed-off-by: georgewhewell <georgerw@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/thunderbolt/xdomain.c | 14 ++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/thunderbolt/xdomain.c b/drivers/thunderbolt/xdomain.c
index 781d88d06b93..322e243fa7d9 100644
--- a/drivers/thunderbolt/xdomain.c
+++ b/drivers/thunderbolt/xdomain.c
@@ -2594,6 +2594,7 @@ bool tb_xdomain_handle_request(struct tb *tb, enum tb_cfg_pkg_type type,
 	const struct tb_protocol_handler *handler, *tmp;
 	const struct tb_xdp_header *hdr = buf;
 	unsigned int length;
+	bool matched = false;
 	int ret = 0;
 
 	/* We expect the packet is at least size of the header */
@@ -2619,6 +2620,7 @@ bool tb_xdomain_handle_request(struct tb *tb, enum tb_cfg_pkg_type type,
 		if (!uuid_equal(&hdr->uuid, handler->uuid))
 			continue;
 
+		matched = true;
 		mutex_unlock(&xdomain_lock);
 		ret = handler->callback(buf, size, handler->data);
 		mutex_lock(&xdomain_lock);
@@ -2628,6 +2630,18 @@ bool tb_xdomain_handle_request(struct tb *tb, enum tb_cfg_pkg_type type,
 	}
 	mutex_unlock(&xdomain_lock);
 
+	if (!matched) {
+		const u32 *w = buf;
+		size_t n = size / 4;
+
+		pr_info_ratelimited("tb xdomain: unmatched uuid=%pUb cfg_type=%d size=%zu xdp_type=0x%x w[0..7]=%08x %08x %08x %08x %08x %08x %08x %08x\n",
+				    &hdr->uuid, type, size, hdr->type,
+				    n > 0 ? w[0] : 0, n > 1 ? w[1] : 0,
+				    n > 2 ? w[2] : 0, n > 3 ? w[3] : 0,
+				    n > 4 ? w[4] : 0, n > 5 ? w[5] : 0,
+				    n > 6 ? w[6] : 0, n > 7 ? w[7] : 0);
+	}
+
 	return ret > 0;
 }
 
